Section 29. Monitoring and Evaluation.

Pursuant to Section 14 of the FSL Act, the FSL Inter-Agency Council (composed of one representative each from the Commission on Human Rights, Children's Welfare Council, the Philippine Commission on Women, Komisyon sa Wikang Filipino, and FSL organizations), as the oversight body on FSL concerns, shall act as catalyst for implementing FSl and shall:

a. act as primary coordinating body on FSL concerns;

b. serve as over-all monitoring body and oversight to ensure the implementation of the Act and these Rules and Regulations. In doing so, the Inter-Agency Council may direct other government agencies and instrumentalities, as may be necessary, to attend the meetings and report on the implementation of the Act and these Rules and Regulations and for them o respond to problems brought to their attention;

c. lead in ensuring the government agencies are made aware of the FSL, and the effective implementation of the Act and these Rules and Regulations;
